+
+  <section class="dual-section">
+    <h2>definition and arithmetic</h2>
+    <p>The dual numbers form the commutative real algebra <code>R[ε]/(ε²)</code>. Every element has the form <code>a + bε</code>.</p>
+    <div class="dual-table-wrap"><table>
+      <thead><tr><th>operation</th><th>rule</th><th>condition / note</th></tr></thead>
+      <tbody>
+        <tr><td>equality</td><td><code>a+bε = c+dε ⇔ a=c and b=d</code></td><td>ε part is independent of real part</td></tr>
+        <tr><td>addition</td><td><code>(a+bε)+(c+dε)=(a+c)+(b+d)ε</code></td><td>componentwise</td></tr>
+        <tr><td>multiplication</td><td><code>(a+bε)(c+dε)=ac+(ad+bc)ε</code></td><td>the <code>bdε²</code> term vanishes</td></tr>
