+      <code>(x+ε)³ = x³ + 3x²ε + 3xε² + ε³ = x³ + 3x²ε</code>. For smooth functions this is the same Taylor-series phenomenon.
+      No limiting process, symbolic simplification, or finite-difference step size is needed.
+    </p>
+    <pre><code>{`function square(x) { return x * x }
+
+square(3 + 1ε) = 9 + 6ε
+// value = 9, derivative at 3 = 6`}</code></pre>
+  </section>
+
+  <section class="dual-columns">
+    <article>
